# ClawQL documentation

**ClawQL** registers **core** tools **`search`** and **`execute`**, plus optional **`sandbox_exec`** (remote code in a Cloudflare Sandbox via bridge), **`memory_ingest`**, and **`memory_recall`** (Obsidian vault), and optional **`ingest_external_knowledge`** (bulk Markdown + optional URL fetch). An internal **GraphQL** projection layer keeps API responses lean for **OpenAPI 3**, **Swagger 2**, and **Google Discovery**. The same tool set is available over **stdio**, **Streamable HTTP**, and (when enabled) **gRPC** via the reusable **[`mcp-grpc-transport`](https://www.npmjs.com/package/mcp-grpc-transport)** package‚Äîsee [Deployment](/deployment) and [Kubernetes](/kubernetes). [Full tool reference (repo)](https://github.com/danielsmithdevelopment/ClawQL/blob/main/docs/mcp-tools.md).&#x20;

Optional **`cache`** (**`CLAWQL_ENABLE_CACHE`**) is **in-process LRU** scratch storage, not the vault ‚Äî [Session cache](/cache), [cache-tool.md](https://github.com/danielsmithdevelopment/ClawQL/blob/main/docs/cache-tool.md). Optional **`audit`** (**`CLAWQL_ENABLE_AUDIT`**) is an in-process event buffer for operator trails ‚Äî **[enterprise-mcp-tools.md](https://github.com/danielsmithdevelopment/ClawQL/blob/main/docs/enterprise-mcp-tools.md)** ([#89](https://github.com/danielsmithdevelopment/ClawQL/issues/89)). Optional **`notify`** (**`CLAWQL_ENABLE_NOTIFY`**) posts to Slack ‚Äî [Slack notify](/notify), [notify-tool.md](https://github.com/danielsmithdevelopment/ClawQL/blob/main/docs/notify-tool.md) ([#77](https://github.com/danielsmithdevelopment/ClawQL/issues/77)). Optional **`knowledge_search_onyx`** (**`CLAWQL_ENABLE_ONYX`**) queries **[Onyx](https://www.onyx.app/)** document search ‚Äî [Onyx knowledge search](/onyx-knowledge), [onyx-knowledge-tool.md](https://github.com/danielsmithdevelopment/ClawQL/blob/main/docs/onyx-knowledge-tool.md) ([#118](https://github.com/danielsmithdevelopment/ClawQL/issues/118)). Optional **`ouroboros_*`** tools (**`CLAWQL_ENABLE_OUROBOROS`**) embed the **[Ouroboros library](/ouroboros)** evolutionary loop ‚Äî [clawql-ouroboros.md](https://github.com/danielsmithdevelopment/ClawQL/blob/main/docs/clawql-ouroboros.md) ([#141](https://github.com/danielsmithdevelopment/ClawQL/issues/141)).

## Getting started&#x20;

Install **`clawql-mcp`**, run it on stdio, then point your MCP client (e.g. Cursor or Claude Desktop) at the server. Optionally set **`CLAWQL_SPEC_PATH`**, **`CLAWQL_SPEC_URL`**, or **`CLAWQL_DISCOVERY_URL`**; if you set nothing, ClawQL loads a bundled **multi-provider** merge (see [spec configuration](/spec-configuration) ‚Äî default **`all-providers`** includes Google Cloud, Cloudflare, GitHub, Slack, document APIs, Onyx, and more).&#x20;
